00:17:39.436 --> 00:17:40.810
There's an old
saying that I keep

00:17:40.810 --> 00:17:43.990
coming back to when we're
thinking about this space.

00:17:43.990 --> 00:17:45.830
Sometimes, when building
apps-- and we're

00:17:45.830 --> 00:17:48.040
all guilty of this--
we forget to see

00:17:48.040 --> 00:17:50.880
the forest for the
trees, which is to say,

00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:53.900
we get so focused on that
one thing in front of us

00:17:53.900 --> 00:17:55.630
that we forget
that we're building

00:17:55.630 --> 00:17:58.390
a relationship with the
user across their lives,

00:17:58.390 --> 00:18:01.500
across their technology.

00:18:01.500 --> 00:18:04.450
And to be really valuable, we
should be present in their life

00:18:04.450 --> 00:18:07.460
whenever it makes sense to them.

00:18:07.460 --> 00:18:10.150
To this end, we should
build with ubiquity in mind

00:18:10.150 --> 00:18:13.500
from the beginning and extend
to new form factors over time.

00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:15.472
And the tools and
design knowledge

00:18:15.472 --> 00:18:17.180
